
                                                                   GETTYPE(2)

   NAME
     gettype - Returns an integer representation of the argument type

   SYNOPSIS
     int gettype (mixed item);

   DESCRIPTION
     Given the argument, returns an integer value representing the type.

          IS_UNDEFINED   -1   IS_NULL         0      IS_INT
     1   IS_STRING  2      IS_OBJECT  3   IS_POINTER      4      IS_ARRAY
     4   IS_MAPPING      5      IS_FLOAT   6   IS_FUNCTION     7
          IS_UNKNOWN     -2

     See Also:
        strtype, comptype

